Huawei is bringing a range of fantastic new devices to South Africa in July. This includes the stylish new Huawei Y6p smartphone, the impressive Huawei Watch GT2e and the powerful Huawei MatePad T8. Leading online retailer Technomobi is offering great deals on these devices, which are available to order right now. The Huawei Y6p smartphone boasts an exquisite design and impressive components at an affordable price. Its wide range of premium features include: The Y6p comes in three colours – Phantom Purple, Midnight Black and Emerald Green. Be sure to order yours early, as the first 50 buyers will get a free wireless Bluetooth headset. Huawei’s latest update to its successful smartwatch line-up comes packed with hardware and features for fitness enthusiasts and gadget lovers alike. The Watch GT2e offers the following capabilities: The first 50 customers to order a Watch GT2e will also receive a Huawei Body Fat Scale and Huawei Sport Bluetooth Headphones worth R1,799. Those that need a powerful tablet have to look no further than the Huawei MatePad T8. The MatePad T8 boasts an 8-inch 1,280 x 800 display in a compact, lightweight design, making it perfect for doing work or watching your favourite TV shows while on the go. Additionally, the MatePad T8 offers the following hardware and features: You will get a Huawei MatePad Cover and Huawei Bluetooth Speaker if you are one of the first 50 people to order your MatePad T8 from Technomobi. Click on one of the links below to visit the Technomobi online store. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-358015" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Artboard-47.png" alt="Huawei Y6P Phantom Purple" width="640" height="640" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Artboard-47.png 2001w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Artboard-47-400x400.png 400w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/Artboard-47-430x430.png 430w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news